WorldStage Newsonline– Universal Insurance Plc, a major player in Nigeria’s insurance sector has released its consolidated statements of financial position as at 31 December 2020 with 80.63% increase in gross premium written to N3.378 billion from N1.870 billion in same period in 2019. The company recorded a 1645.87% rise in profit after taxation to N1.136 billion from N65.073 million in 2019. WorldStage earlier reported Universal Insurance’s statements of comprehensive income for the period ended 30 Sept ember 2020 with a decline in gross premium written to N539.928 million in Q3 2020 from N596.436 million in 2019.